*mpg123-0.59s-r3 (12 Apr 2004)

  12 Apr 2004; Jeremy Huddleston <eradicator@gentoo.org>
  mpg123-0.59s-r3.ebuild:
  Support for more nas and esd added.  Alsa is broken.  Closes bug #47269.

  18 Feb 2004; Martin Schlemmer <azarah@gentoo.org> mpg123-0.59s-r2.ebuild:
  Remove -m486 based on patch from Thomas Veith <th_veith@web.de>, closing bug
  #41021. Also remove the added -O2, and fix build to always use our CFLAGS -
  there was an issue with USE=mmx that CFLAGS was not set.

  18 Feb 2004; Martin Holzer <mholzer@gentoo.org> mpg123-0.59s-r2.ebuild:
  adding IUSE. Closes 41890

  17 Feb 2004; Joshua Kinard <kumba@gentoo.org> mpg123-0.59r-r2.ebuild,
  mpg123-0.59r-r3.ebuild, mpg123-0.59s-r2.ebuild:
  Masked on mips until further notice. This package does appear to have the
  capability to compile on mips, but it requires a dep on the alsa driver, and
  attempts to compile have so far failed. Will look into it later.

